==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Phenol phthalein
<hw>Phenol
phthalein</hw>.</mhw>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A white or
yellowish white crystalline substance, <chform>C20H14O4</chform>, formed
by condensation of the anhydride of phthalic acid and phenol. Its
solution in alkalies is brilliant red, but is decolorized by acids. This
reaction, being very delicate, is used as a pH indicator. It is
sometimes used as a laxative in veterinary medicine.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Phenomenal</ent>⟦br⟧
